players.name: Rhys Bennett
players.bio: Rhys Joseph Bennett, the English defender for Manchester United, showcases a well-rounded skill set. His notable crossing ability and strong defensive presence make him a valuable asset on the field. Bennett's proficiency in aerial duels, coupled with his composed tackling style, bolsters the team's backline. With a keen sense of positioning and commendable work ethic, he contributes both defensively and offensively. A disciplined player, Bennett's clean tackling style exemplifies his commitment to the game.
players.analysis: Denton-born and bred, the under-18s captain at Manchester United, Bennett, debuted in the 2020/21 season against Blackburn Rovers. Leading the team to the FA Youth Cup in 2021/22, he's a well-grounded centre-back who regularly visits his primary school in Denton. Thrilled by every Old Trafford appearance, Bennett embraces the dream, vowing to give his all and cherishing each moment on the iconic pitch.

players.name: Jobe Bellingham
players.bio: Jobe Samuel Bellingham, the English attacking midfielder for AFC Sunderland, exhibits remarkable potential, standing out for his considerable crossing prowess. With a dominant right foot and significant dribbling ability, he brings a high level of finesse to the field. Bellingham's game is characterized by exceptional vision, composure, and a strong work ethic. His impressive acceleration, agility, and resilience make him a standout prospect in the football world.
players.analysis: Jobe Samuel Patrick Bellingham, born on September 23, 2005, is a talented English footballer excelling as a midfielder or forward for EFL Championship's Sunderland. Rising through Birmingham City's academy, he made his mark in the 2021–22 season, showcasing his skills and earning a professional contract. Bellingham's journey continued with Sunderland in 2023, where his prowess on the field is making waves. Additionally, he has represented England at various youth levels, demonstrating his promising international career.

players.name: Lennon Miller
players.analysis: Lennon Miller, the Scottish midfielder for Motherwell FC, possesses a remarkable potential of 85. With a predominantly right foot, Miller showcases a notable ability in crossing and short passing. His agility and acceleration make him agile on the field, complemented by a commendable vision for the game. While his defensive skills may benefit from improvement, Miller's overall versatility and promising potential position him as an asset in the midfield.
players.bio: Lennon Miller, born on 25 August 2006, is a Scottish midfielder for Motherwell. Making history at 16 as Motherwell's youngest player, he debuted in a Scottish League Cup victory. His Scottish Premiership journey started against Rangers in 2022, followed by a crucial appearance against Celtic in 2023. In the 2023–24 season, he began as a regular but faced a red card against Livingston. Internationally, he dazzled with a Goal of the Year for Scotland's under-16s. The son of former Scotland international Lee Miller, Lennon overcame personal loss and impressed at Coltness High School.

players.name: Charlie Savage
players.analysis: Charlie Savage, the Welsh midfielder from Reading FC, possesses a well-rounded skill set. His standout ability lies in precise crossing, making him a valuable asset on the offensive front. With a left-footed prowess and adept dribbling, Savage seamlessly navigates the pitch. A technically proficient player, he showcases finesse in both passing and set-piece execution. His defensive attributes, marked by solid tackling and positional awareness, contribute to a versatile and reliable presence on the field. Savage's game is defined by a strategic vision and a commendable level of composure, making him a notable midfielder for Reading FC.
players.bio: Charlie William Henry Savage, born on May 2, 2003, is a talented midfielder for EFL EFL League One's Reading and the Wales national team. Following his father Robbie Savage's footsteps, he began his football journey at Manchester United. Savage made his professional debut with United in the 2021-22 UEFA Champions League. After a stint with Forest Green Rovers in 2022-23, he signed a four-year contract with Reading in July 2023, showcasing his prowess with a goal in August. Savage, a versatile central midfielder, combines defensive strength with attacking flair, distinguishing himself from his father's playing style. He has represented Wales at various youth levels and earned his first senior cap in October 2023.

players.name: Bailey Rice
players.analysis: At 17, Bailey Rice shines in Scottish football, making significant contributions to the Rangers. His unique left foot and skillful feints showcase exceptional technical prowess for his age. Offensively, Rice displays short-pass precision and admirable vision. Despite his youth, he captains Scotland's U20s, revealing not just talent but early leadership. Versatile in defense, he shows solid tackling abilities. With notable speed and agility, Rice navigates the field effortlessly. The future looks promising for this young Scottish talent, hinting at a bright trajectory as he continues to develop.
players.bio: Born on October 4, 2006, Scottish footballer Bailey Rice plays for Rangers in the Scottish Premiership. A Motherwell youth academy product, Rice joined Rangers on June 30, 2022, rejecting a contract with Motherwell. Making his senior debut in February 2023 against Livingston, he became Rangers' youngest post-war league player at 16 years and 137 days, second only to Derek Ferguson in all competitions.

players.name: Oli McBurnie
players.analysis: Oliver McBurnie, is a key player for Sheffield United, bringing notable skills, particularly in finishing and aerial play. His combativeness and leadership are highlighted, providing essential motivation to the team. With the ability to make an immediate impact, McBurnie stands out as an influential figure, not just for his technical talent but also for the inspiration he brings to the team.
players.bio: Oliver Robert McBurnie, born on June 4, 1996, is a seasoned professional footballer renowned for his role as a striker with Sheffield United in the Premier League and the Scotland national team. With his roots in youth football at Leeds United, McBurnie initiated his career at Bradford City, undertaking two loan stints at Chester. Subsequently joining Swansea City, he gained valuable experience through loan spells at Newport County, Bristol Rovers, and Barnsley. Despite being born in England, McBurnie proudly represents Scotland on the international stage, marking his senior debut in March 2018.

players.name: Ashley Young
players.analysis: Ashley Young, a seasoned English veteran at 37, brings a wealth of experience, notably gained during his triumphant spell at Manchester United. His standout crossing ability, paired with astute dribbling, provides Everton with a potent attacking edge. Young's right foot, a reliable asset, complements his exceptional crossing prowess. Beyond offensive contributions, his defensive aptitude shines in tackles and interceptions. A leader with sharp vision and composed demeanor, Young adds both technical prowess and a winning mentality to Everton's roster, promising a valuable impact.
players.bio: Ashley Simon Young, born on July 9, 1985, is an English professional footballer, currently a full-back for Everton in the Premier League. Starting as a winger at Watford, he rose to prominence in their promotion-winning 2005–06 season. Young has had successful stints with Aston Villa, Manchester United, and Inter Milan, winning multiple trophies. He returned to Aston Villa in 2021 before joining Everton in 2023. Young earned 39 caps for England, featuring in Euro 2012 and the 2018 World Cup.

players.name: Luke Harris
players.analysis: Luke Harris, the talented Welsh player from Fulham FC, is emerging as one of the brightest prospects in English and Welsh football. His remarkable crossing ability stands out, providing a valuable contribution in the offensive realm. With a powerful right foot and admirable dribbling skills, Harris shows significant potential to become a dynamic force on the field. His defensive prowess and impressive agility add to his multifaceted skill set. Endorsed by Ryan Giggs, Harris is on a promising trajectory in the sports arena.
players.bio: Luke Harris, born on March 4, 2005, is a talented midfielder for Premier League side Fulham and the Wales under-21 national team. Hailing from Jersey, he attended St. Clement School and made waves with a remarkable hat-trick for Fulham's under-23s in February 2022. Harris secured a professional contract until 2025 and made his Premier League debut in October 2022. Recognized as the 'Rising Star' at the 2022 Channel Islands Sports Awards, he has also represented Wales at various age levels, earning a senior call-up in September 2022.

players.name: Elliot Watt
players.bio: Elliot William Watt, born on March 11, 2000, is a professional midfielder for EFL League Two club Salford City. Starting his career in Liverpool's youth academy, he later joined Blackburn Rovers and Preston North End before signing his first professional contract with Wolverhampton Wanderers in 2017. Watt made his Wolves debut in 2018 and had a loan spell at Carlisle United in 2020. Joining Bradford City in 2020, he impressed, earning praise from manager Stuart McCall. In 2022, Watt signed a two-year contract with Salford City, earning a spot in the EFL League Two Team of the Season for 2022–23 alongside teammate Ibou Touray. Representing Scotland at various youth levels, Watt's dynamic career continues to flourish.

players.name: Harvey Vale
players.bio: Harvey James Vale, born on September 11, 2003, is a dynamic English footballer excelling as an attacking midfielder or forward. Currently on loan from Chelsea to Bristol Rovers, he began his career at Crowborough FC before joining Chelsea's youth ranks. Vale made his Chelsea debut in December 2021 and earned the academy player of the year award in May 2022. With international experience at various youth levels, including captaining England U19 to victory in the 2022 UEFA European Under-19 Championship, Vale continues to showcase his talent and versatility.
players.analysis: Harvey Vale, the talented English midfielder for Bristol Rovers, showcases a left-footed prowess on the field. With an impressive blend of agility and acceleration, Vale maneuvers through opponents with finesse. His vision on the pitch, coupled with composed attacks, amplifies the team's strategic edge. Noteworthy ball control and precise passing, especially in short distances, underline his technical finesse. Vale's adeptness in free kicks and his capability to contribute defensively further solidify his multifaceted impact on the game.

players.name: Sammy Braybrooke
players.bio: Samuel Charles Braybrooke, born on March 12, 2004, is an English midfielder for EFL Championship's Sheffield United. Hailing from Wigston, scouted by Bill Ward at Oadby Owls, he joined Leicester Academy and stands out at 5ft 7in. Known as "Modric" and "Leicester Iniesta," Braybrooke signed a pro contract until 2024. Making his debut in November 2022, he faced a setback with an anterior cruciate ligament injury in February 2023. An England U19 captain, he briefly gained attention in Mexico due to documentation errors.
players.analysis: Sammy Brayboroke, the English midfielder from Sheffield United, boasts a commendable overall skill set. Renowned for his exceptional ball control and precise short passing, Brayboroke orchestrates plays with finesse. His adeptness in long passing adds strategic depth to his game, while a balanced combination of agility and reactions enhances his on-field responsiveness. Additionally, his defensive capabilities shine through well-timed standing tackles and marked composure. A reliable playmaker, Brayboroke's prowess contributes significantly to the team's dynamic playstyle.

players.name: Ronnie Edwards
players.analysis: Ronnie Edwards, the English defender for Peterborough United, is a robust force in the backline. With a solid overall rating, his standout attributes lie in exceptional defensive prowess. Edwards showcases impeccable marking and tackling skills, making him a formidable opponent for any striker. His physical strength and aerial ability, coupled with swift sprint speed, contribute to a well-rounded defensive presence. Edwards' proficiency in defensive fundamentals makes him a stalwart asset for the team.
players.bio: Ronnie Lee Edwards, born on March 28, 2003, is an English professional footballer and defender for Peterborough United. Beginning his journey at Barnet's academy at the age of nine, Edwards swiftly rose through the ranks. His senior debut at sixteen showcased his talent. After five appearances for Barnet, he joined Peterborough United in August 2020. Edwards made significant contributions, earning his place in the England U19 and U20 squads, winning the 2022 UEFA European Under-19 Championship and representing England in the 2023 FIFA U-20 World Cup.

players.name: Andrew Moran
players.analysis: Andrew Moran, the versatile Irish midfielder/forward currently on loan at Blackburn Rovers from Brighton & Hove Albion, brings dynamism to the pitch. With a right-footed prowess, Moran showcases finesse with 3/5 skill moves. Noteworthy for his acceleration, agility, and balance, Moran's technical finesse shines in ball control and short passing. His flair on the field adds a touch of creativity, complementing his solid vision and composure. Moran's game reflects a blend of speed, skill, and playmaking acumen.
players.bio: Andrew Edwards Moran, born on October 15, 2003, is an Irish midfielder for EFL Championship's Blackburn Rovers, on loan from Premier League's Brighton & Hove Albion. He made history as Bray Wanderers' youngest player and scorer before joining Brighton's academy in July 2020. Moran debuted for Brighton's first team in August 2021, signing a three-year extension in 2022. His international journey includes captaining Ireland's youth teams and making his senior debut in November 2023.

players.name: Bali Mumba
players.bio: Bali Alef Mumba, born on October 8, 2001, is an English professional footballer excelling as a full-back for Plymouth Argyle in the EFL Championship. Starting at Sunderland, he became their youngest captain in 2018. After a stint with Norwich City, he contributed significantly to Peterborough United's FA Cup triumph on loan. His impactful loan to Plymouth Argyle saw him clinch the EFL League One title. Mumba secured a permanent move to Plymouth in July 2023, showcasing his versatility and goal-scoring prowess. Internationally, he has represented England across various age groups.
players.analysis: Bali Mumba, the dynamic English wing-back from Plymouth Argyle, brings a unique blend of agility and acceleration to the pitch. His exceptional balance and ball control make him a formidable force on the wing, while his precise crossing ability amplifies his impact in the attacking third. Mumba's defensive prowess, marked by solid standing and sliding tackles, adds resilience to his game. A player with remarkable versatility, Mumba's skillful dribbling and vision make him a valuable asset on both ends of the field.

players.name: Luke Cundle
players.bio: Luke James Cundle, born on 26 April 2002, is an English footballer currently shining as an attacking midfielder for Premier League Wolverhampton Wanderers. Graduating from Wolves' academy, he marked his debut in a 2019 EFL Cup victory against Reading. Cundle's noteworthy moments include appearances in the Premier League Asia Trophy Final and his Premier League debut in a 3–1 triumph over Southampton. His ascent continues with a full Premier League debut in a 2–0 victory against Tottenham Hotspur on 13 February 2022.
players.analysis: Luke Cundle, the English midfielder for Wolves, showcases a well-rounded skill set on the field. His adept ball control and precise short passing contribute to a fluid offensive game, complemented by an agile and balanced movement style. Cundle's acceleration and vision make him an asset in creating scoring opportunities. Additionally, his composed demeanor underlines his reliability in crucial moments. While he may need improvement in defensive aspects, his promising potential suggests a player poised for growth and impact.

players.name: Todd Cantwell
players.bio: Todd Owen Cantwell, born on February 27, 1998, is an English midfielder currently playing for Rangers in the Scottish Premiership. He started his career at Norwich City, making his senior debut in January 2018 and accumulating 129 appearances over six seasons. Cantwell also had loan spells at Fortuna Sittard and AFC Bournemouth. In January 2023, he joined Rangers. Cantwell has represented England at the under-17 and under-21 levels, showcasing his talent internationally.
players.analysis: Todd Cantwell, the skilled English midfielder for Rangers, brings finesse to the field. His standout attribute lies in impeccable ball control, coupled with a remarkable flair for first-touch play. With a potent combination of agility and acceleration, Cantwell maneuvers through opponents effortlessly, showcasing his impressive dribbling skills. His vision on the field is exemplary, contributing to his ability to position himself strategically, making him a valuable asset in the attacking lineup.

teams.name: Salford City
teams.summary: Salford City FC, owned by the Class of '92 (Neville, Scholes, Giggs, Butt, Beckham), competes in English football leagues.

wiki: Founded in 1940, Salford City Football Club has a rich and diverse history spanning over seven decades. Located in Salford, Greater Manchester, the club has always had a close connection with the neighboring and renowned football city, Manchester.

During its early decades, Salford City competed in various regional leagues and achieved notable successes in local competitions. While it may not have reached national spotlight, the club was a valuable part of the local community, providing fans with exciting moments.

However, it was from 2014 that Salford City entered a new chapter in its history. In this year, the club was acquired by a notable consortium known as the 'Class of 92.' Comprising former Manchester United players - Gary Neville, Ryan Giggs, Nicky Butt, Phil Neville, and Paul Scholes - along with businessman Peter Lim, owner of Valencia in Spain, this group brought a new vision and significant resources to the club.

In a further significant development, in 2019, the iconic former player David Beckham, a member of the 'Class of 92,' acquired a 10% stake in the club. His entry into the shareholder board brought even more prestige and resources to Salford City, solidifying the commitment of football's big names to the club's future success.

The entry of the 'Class of 92' and the addition of David Beckham mark a transformative moment for Salford City. Substantial investments were made in infrastructure, facilities, and, crucially, in the player roster. The goal was clear: to elevate the club to higher echelons of English football.

In the following years, Salford City experienced a meteoric rise through the ranks of English football divisions. Achieving consecutive titles and promotions, the club swiftly moved from lower levels to non-professional leagues, establishing itself as a formidable opponent.

This remarkable trajectory culminated in a historic milestone in 2019 when Salford City secured promotion to the Football League for the first time in the club's history. The team earned this honor by winning the National League play-offs, securing their place in the fourth tier of English football.

This achievement not only marked a moment of triumph for the club but also stood as a testament to the commitment and vision of the "Class of 92" in transforming Salford City into a respected force in the English football landscape. The club is now poised to take on new challenges and script the next chapter of its history in the world of football.

managers.name: Ole Gunnar Solskjær
managers.bio: Ole Gunnar Solskjær, born on February 26, 1973, in Kristiansund, is a former Norwegian footballer and coach who is currently at the helm of the Salford City FC project aiming for the Premier League. During his playing career, he distinguished himself at Manchester United, where he became an icon, recognized as a "supersub" for his effectiveness as a substitute. His fame reached its peak when he scored the decisive goal in the UEFA Champions League final in 1998–99, contributing to the memorable comeback against Bayern Munich.

managers.name: Roberto De Zerbi
managers.bio: Roberto De Zerbi, a former Italian football player, now renowned coach, currently leads Premier League club Brighton & Hove Albion. After a playing career that included stints at AC Milan and Napoli, De Zerbi transitioned to coaching, leaving his mark at clubs like Palermo, Benevento, Sassuolo, and Shakhtar Donetsk. Known for his attacking style, he joined Brighton in the 2022-23 season, achieving historic success with a top-seven finish and qualifying for the UEFA Europa League.

managers.name: Shannon Ruth
managers.bio: Shannon Ruth, currently senior professional development coach at Albion, assumed the role in February 2021 as interim-coach alongside Andrew Crofts, succeeding Simon Rusk. Having started as Albion’s under-21 assistant coach in 2018, Ruth's journey includes coaching stints at Chelsea, Aldershot, and Reading, with a focus on goalkeeping. A seasoned figure in football, he rose through the ranks, eventually becoming interim assistant head coach after key departures. Ruth's dedication led to his recent promotion as under-21s head coach in September 2022 under Roberto De Zerbi.

playStyles.name: Power Shot

playStyles.name: Chip Shot
playStyles.info: A player who is known to often try to chip the goalkeeper when shooting at goal.

playStyles.name: Finesse Shot
playStyles.info: A player who is known to try and place the ball when shooting at goal.

playStyles.name: Power Header
playStyles.info: A player who is known to strike with power when heading towards goal.

playStyles.name: Pinged Pass
playStyles.info: A player who is known for making high-speed ground passes.

playStyles.name: Incisive Pass
playStyles.info: A player who is known for making defence splitting passes for a teammate to run onto.

playStyles.name: Long Ball Pass
playStyles.info: A player who is known for performing lobbed long passes to teammates.

playStyles.name: Tiki Taka
playStyles.info: A player who is known for making first-time accurate and short passes.

playStyles.name: Whipped Pass
playStyles.info: A player who is known for making high-speed whipped crosses into the box.

playStyles.name: First Touch
playStyles.info: A player who is known for accurate first touch control in difficult situations.

playStyles.name: Flair
playStyles.info: A player who is known to try flamboyant moves (traps, passes, and shots).

playStyles.name: Press Proven
playStyles.info: A player who is known for keeping ball possession under physical pressure from the opponent.

playStyles.name: Rapid
playStyles.info: A player who is known to use speed and knock the ball ahead of their opponent to beat them whilst dribbling.

playStyles.name: Technical
playStyles.info: A player who regularly tries to beat an opponent by using technical dribbling ability (with little to no use of skill moves or little to no physical contact).

playStyles.name: Trickster
playStyles.info: A player who is known for being able to perform skill moves in 1v1 situations.

playStyles.name: Block
playStyles.info: A player who is known for performing elastic and overreaching blocks.

playStyles.name: Bruiser
playStyles.info: A player who is known for winning possession by physical imposition.

playStyles.name: Intercept
playStyles.info: A player who is known for performing interceptions and keeping ball possession.

playStyles.name: Jockey
playStyles.info: A player who is known for being successful in 1v1 situations.

playStyles.name: Slide Tackle
playStyles.info: A player who is known for often performing slide tackles.

playStyles.name: Anticipate
playStyles.info: A player who is known for having a high success rate getting ball possession on tackles with a low fouling rate.

playStyles.name: Acrobatic
playStyles.info: A player who tends to perform acrobatic passes, clearances, and shots.

playStyles.name: Aerial
playStyles.info: A player who is known for having a high success rate winning aerial battles in both offence and defence.

playStyles.name: Trivela
playStyles.info: A player who is known for passing, crossing and shooting with the outside of the foot.

playStyles.name: Relentless
playStyles.info: A player who is known for covering a greater area of the field compared to other players in the same position.

playStyles.name: Quick Step
playStyles.info: A player who is known to have a quick burst of speed when accelerating on and off the ball.

playStyles.name: Long Throw
playStyles.info: A player who is known to throw the ball further than the average player.

playStyles.name: Far Throw
playStyles.info: Goalkeeper can target players further away with thrown passes.

playStyles.name: Footwork
playStyles.info: Goalkeeper will perform saves with their feet more frequently.

playStyles.name: Cross Claimer
playStyles.info: Goalkeeper will try to intercept a cross if they can get to it slightly before the opponent.

playStyles.name: Rush Out
playStyles.info: Goalkeeper is more aggressive when coming out of the box to gather over-the-top balls or long through balls.

playStyles.name: Far Reach
playStyles.info: BAG exclusive - BAG players are more effective at saving shots from outside the box with increased reach and jumping.

playStyles.name: Quick Reflexes
playStyles.info: BAG exclusive - BAG players have increased reflexes and reactions when saving shots from inside the box.
